# Constant Fold JSON Functions

## Description

Evaluates JSON functions at compile time when the JSON document and
path arguments are all constants. JSON_EXTRACT('{"a":1}', '$.a')
becomes 1.

**When to apply**: JSON function with constant document and path arguments.

**Why it works**: JSON parsing and path extraction are expensive. When
the document is a literal, the result is known at plan time.

## Implementation

```rust
rw!("fold-json-extract";
    "(json_extract ?doc ?path)" => { FoldJsonExtract("?doc", "?path") }
    if both_const("?doc", "?path")
),
rw!("fold-json-typeof";
    "(json_typeof ?doc)" => { FoldJsonTypeof("?doc") }
    if is_const("?doc")
),
rw!("fold-json-array-length";
    "(json_array_length ?doc)" => { FoldJsonArrayLen("?doc") }
    if is_const("?doc")
),
```

## Test Cases

```sql
-- Before
SELECT JSON_EXTRACT('{"name":"Alice","age":30}', '$.name') FROM t;
-- After
SELECT '"Alice"' FROM t;
```

```sql
-- Negative: column JSON document
SELECT JSON_EXTRACT(metadata, '$.key') FROM events;
-- Cannot fold: metadata is a column
```

